@node "WSTEP_eng" "INTRODUCTION"
@next "WYMAGANIA_eng"
@prev "O_AUTORZE_eng"

The  great  word  processor,  Final Writer, uses its own typefaces.  You can
also  use  your  system installed Intellifonts in FW, though when you do so,
the  tools  which are responsible for applying the bold and/or italic styles
to  a  font  stop functioning.  It happens so because when you want to apply
the bold style to a typeface, Final Writer takes the font's actual name (eg.
CS_Times),  adds  "_Italic"  to  it (CS-Times_Italic) and then tries to read
such  a font.  Yet when it comes to the system installed Intellifonts, files
that  you  have  to  import to the word processor have the extension ".font"
(eg.   CS-Times.font)  and  when  you try to italicize the font, the program
tries    to    read    the    font    ending    with   ".font_Italic"   (eg.
CS-Times.font_Italic),  obviously  to  no  avail.   The  program  should try
reading  eg.  CS-Times_Italic.font instead of CS-Times.font_Italic.  To make
it  do so, use the four Arexx scripts in this archive.  They were written on
the  basis  of  scripts  included  with Final Copy II and Final Writer which
applied  a  certain style to the typeface with the method that the very same
word  processor used (which makes me wonder why the scripts were included if
they only copied the program's functions???).

@endnode

@node "WYMAGANIA_eng" "REQUIREMENTS"
@next "INSTALACJA_eng"
@prev "WSTEP_eng"

   - Amiga (this should be quite obvious)
   - Final Writer
   - Arexx (included in the system since version 2.xx)
   - Intellifonts

@endnode

@node "INSTALACJA_eng" "INSTALLATION"
@next "PROBLEMY_eng"
@prev "WYMAGANIA_eng"

1. Copy  the following  scripts:  Ifont_Plain, Ifont_Bold, Ifont_Italic and
   Ifont_BoldItalic  to  FWMacros  drawer  which  is  in  your Final Writer
   drawer.

2  Run Final Writer,  and add four new buttons to the tool strip:   P , @{b}B@{ub} ,
   @{i}I@{ui} , @{b}@{i}B@{ub}@{ui} and respectively, use the following scripts with them: Ifont_Plain,
   Ifont_Bold, Ifont_Italic  and  Ifont_BoldItalic  (with their full paths,
   of course).

3. Save the configuration to the disk.

4. Run any File Manager and change all fonts' names ending with ".font" and
   ".otag" (do NOT touch the files in _Bullet_Outlines directory - the ones
   with the ".type" extention) like the following:

  FontName.font
  FontName.otag
  FontName_Bold.font
  FontName_Bold.otag
  FontName_Italic.font
  FontName_Italic.otag
  FontName_BoldItalic.font
  FontName_BoldItalic.otag

  for example:

  CS-TimesPL.font
  CS-TimesPL.otag
  CS-TimesPL_Bold.font
  CS-TimesPL_Bold.otag
  CS-TimesPL_Italic.font
  CS-TimesPL_Italic.otag
  CS-TimesPL_BoldItalic.font
  CS-TimesPL_BoldItalic.otag

5. Done !!!

@endnode

@node "PROBLEMY_eng" "PROBLEMS"
@next "OSTRZEZENIE_eng"
@prev "INSTALACJA_eng"

1. Scripts do not run.

Check if Arexx is running - run RexxMast.

Check  if  your  script directory is not at too a deep level - if it is, try
putting  scripts eg.  in SYS:S/ directory and then change the paths in Final
Writer.

2. Fonts are not being read.

Check if the fonts have the right names (see @{"Installation" link "INSTALACJA_eng" 0} part) - and change
their names.

@endnode

